[{"location":"#ORCAExample.jl","page":"Home","title":"ORCAExample.jl","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"This is a small example package that was created for the Astronomical Software Development workshop (ORCA?) in New York City in May 2022. The package is intended to demonstrate a minimal example of a Julia package equipped with unit testing, continuous integration (via GitHub Workflows), and a documentation website (via Documenter.jl).","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"The package can be installed at the Julia REPL by typing ] to access the Pkg.jl REPL:","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"(@v1.6) pkg> add https://github.com/elijahmathews/ORCAExample.jl.git","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Alternatively, the following can be run at the Julia REPL:","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"julia> import Pkg; Pkg.add(url=\"https://github.com/elijahmathews/ORCAExample.jl.git\")","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"This currently has one function available:","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"julia> using ORCAExample\n\njulia> ORCAExample.greet()\nHello World!","category":"page"},{"location":"#API","page":"Home","title":"API","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"ORCAExample.greet","category":"page"},{"location":"#ORCAExample.greet","page":"Home","title":"ORCAExample.greet","text":"greet()\n\nDisplay a \"hello world\" greeting to the user.\n\nExamples\n\njulia> ORCAExample.greet()\nHello World!\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"}]
